law.text:
No person shall:
Display or cause or permit to be displayed or have in his possession any operator's license knowing it to be fictitious or to have been canceled, revoked, suspended or altered;
Lend to, or knowingly permit the use of by, one not entitled to, any operator's license issued to the person so lending or permitting the use of the license;
Represent as one's own any operator's license not issued to the person displaying the license;
Fail to surrender to the cabinet upon demand, any operator's license which has been suspended, canceled or revoked;
Use a false name or give a false address in any application for an operator's license or any renewal or duplicate, or knowingly make a false statement or knowingly conceal a material fact or otherwise commit a fraud in any application.
